body:
@F3PiX the blog posts are posted by Team prodyoGEEKY and as you can see on [thir profile page](https://teams.railsgirlssummerofcode.org/teams/338), they are the ones referencing a railsgirlssummerofcode.org blog post. It was not added to the Teams App by the orga team.

> 2. the way we pull in blogposts from the orga website.

Yes, that's the reason. See https://github.com/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/issues/901#issuecomment-354977203 above: the Atom/RSS URL is automatically extracted in `lib/feed.rb`. I'm currently adding a quick fix to allow a single web page as a `Source` that won't be interpreted as a feed.
